<subsection xml:id="subsec-combined-operations-of-integers-on-a-number-line">
    <title>Combined Operations of Integers on a Number Line</title>
    <activity>
            <p>
                <alert>Work in groups</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="1. ">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Draw a number line similar to the one shown below.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="combined-operation-1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[thick,&lt; - &gt;](-6.5,0) -- (8.5,0);
                                    \foreach \x in {1,...,8} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {-1,-2,-3,-4,-5,-6} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Starting at <m>(-2)</m> on the number line, move <m>7</m> steps to the right and 
                            then move <m>3</m> steps to left and circle the number at the end of the last step.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Starting at <m>(+2)</m> on the number line, move <m>6</m> steps to the right and then move
                             <m>2</m> steps to left and circle the number at the end of the last step.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Write down the expressions and the final answers of the movements in step <m>2</m> and step <m>3</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Share your results and compare them with other groups in the class.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
    </activity>
    <p><m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m></p>
    <p>
        When solving expressions that involve both addition and subtraction of integers, 
        follow the operations from left to right.
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Adding a <alert>positive integer</alert> means moving to the <alert>right</alert>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Subtracting a <alert>positive integer</alert> means moving to the <alert>left</alert>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Adding a <alert>negative integer</alert> is the same as moving to the <alert>left</alert>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Subtracting a <alert>negative integer</alert> is the same as moving to the <alert>right</alert>.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Example: <m>(-2) + (+5) - (+3)</m>
                    Start at <m>-2</m>, move <m>5</m> steps to the <alert>right</alert> (for <m>+5</m>), 
                    then move <m>3</m> steps to the <alert>left</alert> again since we are subtracting a positive integer.
                </p>
                <image>
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="combined-operation-2"> 
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \draw[&lt;- &gt;](-4.5,0) -- (5.5,0);
                            
                            \foreach \x in {-4,...,-1} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                            }
                            
                            \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                            \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                            
                            \foreach \x in {1,...,5} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                            }
                            % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                            \draw[red,-&gt;] (-2,0.1) to[bend left=60] (-1,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (-1,0.2) to[bend left=60] (0,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (0,0.2) to[bend left=60] (1,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (1,0.2) to[bend left=60] (2,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (2,0.2) to[bend left=60] (3,0.1);

                            % Start label
                            \draw[] (-2,0) -- (-2,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (-2,0.55) {\text{start}};
                            
                            % Stop label
                            \draw[] (3,0) -- (3,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (3,0.55) {\text{stop}};
                            
                            \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (-2,0) circle(0.1);
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
                <image>
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="combined-operation-3">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-4.5,0) -- (5.5,0);
                            
                            \foreach \x in {-4,...,-1} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                            }
                            
                            \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                            \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                            
                            \foreach \x in {1,...,5} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                            }
                            % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                            \draw[red,-&gt;] (3,0.1) to[bend right=60] (2,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (2,0.2) to[bend right=60] (1,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (1,0.2) to[bend right=60] (0,0.1);
                            
                            % Start label
                            \draw[] (3,0) -- (3,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (3,0.55) {\text{start}};
                            
                            % Stop label
                            \draw[] (0,0) -- (0,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (0,0.55) {\text{stop}};
                            
                            \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (3,0) circle(0.1);
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Use a number line to perform the following expression.
            </p>
            <p>
                <m> (+4) - (6) + (3) </m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Starting at <m>(+4)</m>, move <m>6</m> steps to the <alert>left</alert> since we are 
                subtracting <alert>a positive integer</alert> as shown in the number line below.
            </p>
            <image>
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                <latex-image label="combined-operation-example-1">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-4.5,0) -- (5.5,0);
        
                        \foreach \x in {-4,...,-1} {
                            \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                            \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                        }
                        
                        \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                        \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                        
                        \foreach \x in {1,...,5} {
                            \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                            \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                        }
                        % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                        \draw[red,-&gt;] (4,0.1) to[bend right=60] (3,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (3,0.2) to[bend right=60] (2,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (2,0.2) to[bend right=60] (1,0.1);
                        \draw[red,-&gt;] (1,0.1) to[bend right=60] (0,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (0,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-1,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (-1,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-2,0.1);
                        
                        % Start label
                        \draw[] (4,0) -- (4,0.5);
                        \node[above] at (4,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                        
                        % Stop label
                        \draw[] (-2,0) -- (-2,0.5);
                        \node[above] at (-2,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};
                        
                        \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (4,0) circle(0.1);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
            </image>
            <p>
                Then, from <m>(-2)</m> on the number line, move <m>3</m> steps to the right since we are 
                adding a <alert>a positive integer</alert>.
            </p>
            <image>
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                <latex-image label="combined-operation-example-2">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-4.5,0) -- (5.5,0);
        
                        \foreach \x in {-4,...,-1} {
                            \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                            \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                        }
                        
                        \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                        \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                        
                        \foreach \x in {1,...,5} {
                            \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                            \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                        }
                        % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                        \draw[red,-&gt;] (-2,0.1) to[bend left=60] (-1,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (-1,0.2) to[bend left=60] (0,0.1);
                        \draw[red,- &gt;] (0,0.2) to[bend left=60] (1,0.1);
                    
                        % Start label
                        \draw[] (-2,0) -- (-2,0.5);
                        \node[above] at (-2,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                        
                        % Stop label
                        \draw[] (1,0) -- (1,0.5);
                        \node[above] at (1,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};
                        
                        \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (-2,0) circle(0.1);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
            </image>
        </solution>
    </example>
</subsection>